The paper focuses on developing a new analytics operator for smoothing time series visualizations to better prioritize end users' attention. This involves techniques from user interface design, signal processing, and stream processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also deals with data processing and optimization, which suggests categories such as cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of metrics to assess the quality of smoothed plots and the optimization strategy involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
